# Palmoria Group HR Analytics

## 🏢 Case Study Overview
Palmoria, a manufacturing company in Nigeria, is facing scrutiny over gender inequality and salary structure issues. As a data analyst, I was tasked with uncovering these insights and providing actionable recommendations.

## 📊 Tools Used
- Excel (pivot tables, formulas)
- Power BI (optional visuals)
- Data cleaning, modeling, and visual storytelling

## 🔍 Key Analyses
- Gender distribution by department and region
- Pay gap identification by gender, department, and region
- Minimum wage compliance check ($90,000+ rule)
- Salary band segmentation
- Bonus allocation modeling from performance ratings

## 📌 Results
- Identified departments with a gender pay gap
- 17% of employees fell below regulatory pay
- Bonus modeling helped compute fair total compensation
- Full summary and recommendations included

